<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The documentation for Zend_XmlRpc_Server_Fault::attachObserver states that this function takes a class name for a class that has a public static method (observe) that accepts an exception as argument. 
The argument passed to the observe is an instance of Zend_XmlRpc_Server_Fault. Even though exception is spelled with lowercase 'e' and it doesn't say that it is the class Exception this is confusing.</p>

<p>Sollution:
Change the documentation to state that the function observe should take an instance of Zend_XmlRpc_Server_Fault as it's sole argument.</p>

